Date: Thu 25 Sep 2014
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2014; 27(40) [edited] http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=16159


African swine fever, Chad
-------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 25 Sep 2014 from Dr Adyl Bechir, Directeur, Services Veterinaires, Ministere du Developpement Pastoral et des Productions Animales, N'djamena, Chad

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 3 Sep 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 18 Sep 2014
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 31 Dec 2012
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: African swine fever virus
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: 7th district of N'Djamena, Ville de N'Jamena
Date of start of the outbreak: 3 Sep 2014
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Swine / 500 / 96 / 77 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]:
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Swine / 19.20 / 15.40 / 80.21 / 15.40
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: stamping out; disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s)

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Livestock Research Institute for Developement (IRED) from Farcha (National laboratory) / Swine / competitive ELISA (c-ELISA) / 18 Sep 2014 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Data found in the OIE's WAHID database, disease incidence section, shows that in 2010 and 2011 Chad reported 7 and 5 outbreaks of African swine fever, respectively. In 2012, the disease was present, but no quantitative data was provided (http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Diseaseinformation/statusdetail).

Chad, officially the Republic of Chad, is a landlocked country in Central Africa. It is bordered by Libya to the north, Sudan to the east, the Central African Republic to the south, Cameroon and Nigeria to the southwest and Niger to the west (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chad).

This new event is located close to the Cameroon border, where, according to the last available OIE annual report January-December 2013, the disease is reported as "confirmed infection/infestation without clinical signs". See annual report at http://tinyurl.com/nm2nagq.

An administrative map of Chad is available at http://www.ephotopix.com/chad_political_map.html. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2809645,57.]
